bug.short_desc: Provide a locales filter in the resource editor

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86738 editor and problems view crowded by many locales
Provide a way to let a user specify which locales he wants to work on.
This is most probably something Pascal has in mind.
The filter would apply both for the properties being edited and for the generation of markers during the build. The filter would also define the order in which the locales are displayed in the editor.
Use case, a translator for german and italian probably need to only see the default properties and the german and italian values. Other locales are using real-estate in the UI that are a distraction. Also warnings produced by the build that are not related to german and italian make the report less productive.
Attached: a screenshot of what happens with a standard eclipse-platform-nl1 fragment.

Pascal,
Here is the implementation I suggest:
A comma separated list of StringMatchers that can be accessed in the preference page and in a sub-menu of the editor's left-pane.
By default the value is "*", although a non-interporetble value would be considered a wild-card too.
Here are a couple of example values: - "fr,*" would make sure the fr derived locales are displayed immediately after the default properties. All available locales are displayed and validated. Each one is displayed and validated only once. - "fr" would only display the default properties and the fr related locales. Only fr related locales would be validated by the builder. - "*_ca" would select the Canadian related locales.
When the value is changed, a preference-listener is in charge of doing a full build on the projects.
Let me know if this would make sense or what else you would had in mind in this area.
I'd be happy to take a stab at it.

Created attachment 86746 screenshot when displaying only "zh_*, ja"
This demonstrate what the editor and the problem warnings look like when applying the following filter: "zh_*, ja"
The screenshot also shows the new text field in the preferences.

Created attachment 86747 support for filtering locales in the editor and the builder
This patch supports filtering the locales displayed.
When the preference is changed, the index page of the loaded editors is dynamically called and the builder is also called to reflect the change.
Still todo: remove and add the texteditors for the new selection of locales.
This patch is against the current trunk and also contains the last patch filed with bug 214521: https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/attachment.cgi?id=86741
Thanks again for the editor!
This has been committed as part of a another patch.
